<h2 style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Rekenrek</h2>

<div style="line-height:2">
<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Rekenrek consists of two rows of beads; each row has 10 beads. Rekenrek is a visual tool for children to learn about numbers, addition and subtraction.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Click on the beads to slide from right to left to show a number, addition, carry forward, subtraction and borrowing within 20. For example, we can slide 5 beads to show number 5. If 5 and 1 more is 6. To show 10, we can slide all the beads on the top row. The number of the beads slide to the left will be shown in the box at the bottom. Click the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_visibility.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button to make the number appear and disappear.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">To write numbers or cross out beads on the Rekenrek, use the <img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_pencil.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle"> button. Double-click on the button to change the colours of the pencil. Use the <img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_eraser.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle"> or <img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_clear.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle"> button to remove all the scribbles with the pencil tool. To start counting a new set of numbers, click the <img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_reset.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle"> button.</p>
</div>